Function Reference/make clickable « WordPress Codex
-----------

Convert plain text
[URI](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/URI "wikipedia:URI") to
[HTML](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTML "wikipedia:HTML") links.

Converts URI, www, FTP, and email addresses. Finishes by fixing links
within links.

Usage
-----

` <?php make_clickable( $ret ) ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$ret` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Content to convert URIs.
    Default: *None*

Return Values
-------------

 (string) 
:   Content with converted URIs.

Examples
--------

### Display all URLs in clickable links

    <?php 
    $string = "This is a long text that contains some links like http://www.wordpress.org and http://www.wordpress.com .";
    echo make_clickable($string); 
    ?>

Notes
-----

Change Log
----------

Since: 0.71

Source File
-----------

`make_clickable()` is located in `wp-includes/formatting.php`.

